   "source": [
    "1. Why are functions advantagious to have in your programme?.\n",
    "Ans:-Functions reduce the need for duplicate code. This makes programs shorter, easier to read, and easier to update. The main advantage of functions is code Reusability.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "9ccce4a8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "2. When does the code in a function run: when it's specified or when it's called?\n",
    "Ans: The code in a function executes when the function is called, not when the function is specified."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "43653448",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "3. What statement creates a function?\n",
    "Ans: The def statement defines a function"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "f3e5e7d1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def function_name(args):\n",
    "            return args"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "b8e5a9cc",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "4. What is the difference between a function and a function call?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "f74fabcd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Ans : A function is a block of code that does a particular operation and returns a result. \n",
    "while function call can defined as when we have to do any particular task then with the help of above function the function call comes in a picture."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "61e4e265",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "5. How many global scopes are there in a Python program? How many local scopes?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "19979839",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Ans: There is one global scope, and a local scope is created whenever a function is called."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "1c1105c8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "6. What happens to variables in a local scope when the function call returns?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "d09469c4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Ans:- When a function returns, the local scope is destroyed, and all the variables in it are forgotten."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "c42bf464",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "7. What is the concept of a return value? Is it possible to have a return value in an expression?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "f5b0d83d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Ans: A return value is the value that a function call evaluates to. Like any value, a return value can be used as part of an expression."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "ad0bcee4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "8. If a function does not have a return statement, what is the return value of a call to that function?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "9a3061d5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Ans : If there is no return statement for a function,it does not give any result"
   ]
  },
  {
